postcontent: I have a very rare J&R Engineering  Model 80 9mm carbine, NOT a model 68.  This came after the model 68 and was the predecessor to the Wilkinson Arms Linda / Terry carbines.  The M80 differs from the M69 by having the charging handle on the side of the receiver instead of the top.  Another distinsion is the adjustable rear sight and rail mount milled into the top of the receiver.  This particular M80 is unique in that it is stamped as a M68.  ---------     Used in the TV series Hawaii Five-O with Jack Lord and even in a movie with Sal Minio.  This is also the same gun you will find at Grace Land.   Yes, even the KING owned one of these and is on display there.  I am only the second owner of this carbine as it was purchased from an estate sale in 1993.  I have only fire five rounds through it - just to verify it functioned. ------    Carbine comes with one 20 rd and four 30 round magazines and a bunch of spare parts ( four recoil springs, two spring guides, firing pin, extractor, ejector and  parts for the lower).  Just clearing out some of my collection.  The price is high but it is also very rare and this is in mint condition.  I can afford to wait until I find the right buyer -- price is $2150.  Original mags sell for between $75 and $100 each, a complete parts replacement kit - another $500.  So really, you are getting a lot for the money. -----    As I find out more about this carbine - the price will probably go up - price is $2150 - for now price is FIRM.----  Email me and include your phone number - Emails without a phone number will not be answered. ----Additional pictures availableNO TRADES. - EMAILS ASKING FOR TRADE WILL NOT BE ANSWERED
